That error means disable_execute_api_endpoint is being set in a block where the AWS provider schema does not allow it.

Most common causes:

It is in the wrong resource/module block.
The hashicorp/aws provider version is too old for that argument.
disable_execute_api_endpoint is valid on API resources like:

aws_api_gateway_rest_api (REST v1)
aws_apigatewayv2_api (HTTP/WebSocket v2)
If it is inside something like aws_api_gateway_deployment, aws_api_gateway_stage, or a module input not declared by the module, you will get this exact error.

Example (valid placement):
resource "aws_api_gateway_rest_api" "soap" {
  name                         = "soap-api"
  disable_execute_api_endpoint = true
}

Also pin/upgrade provider:
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 4.0"
    }
  }
}

Then run:

tofu init -upgrade
tofu validate
If needed, share the full resource/module block from soap_api.tf; the exact misplaced location can be identified quickly.
